The $M_{\tau\tau}$ distributions reconstructed by SVfit in $WH$ events simulated for a Higgs mass $M = 120$~\GeV
and in simulated $ZH$ events
are shown in Figs.~\ref{fig:perfCompPSvsMEkine_WH_ditau} and~\ref{fig:perfCompFitvsInt_WH_ditau}.
The distributions compare different likelihood models for the tau decay kinematics 
and $M_{\tau\tau}$ solutions obtained by marginalization versus profile likelihood method.
The shape of the distributions is similar to the shape of $M_{\tau\tau}$ distributions reconstructed in 
$Z \rightarrow \tau \tau$ and $M = 130$~\GeV Higgs $\rightarrow \tau \tau$ events 
without additional $W$ bosons ({\it cf.}\ Figs.~\ref{fig:perfCompPSvsMEkine_ditau} and~\ref{fig:perfCompFitvsInt_ditau}).
The presence of an additional neutrino from the $W$ decay degrades the resolution by a bit, but not by much.
In summary, Figs.~\ref{fig:perfCompPSvsMEkine_WH_ditau} and~\ref{fig:perfCompFitvsInt_WH_ditau}
demonstrate the flexibility of the likelihood approach implemented in SVfit to perform well in different use--cases.

